					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">With like 16x24 characters you have to use 8x8 if you don't want to waste tiles</div><br />Personally, I don't mind wasting tiles on sprites. I mean, even if you use all 64 sprites in one frame you will only be using 128 tiles out of the 256 that are available for sprites. If you use CHR-RAM and have a dynamic pattern system that's constantly changing the tiles, the blank tiles will hardly be a problem (and they even compress to nearly nothing, which means almost no PRG-ROM wasted either). With CHR-ROM they'll certainly waste more memory, and you'll need fine bankswitching minimize the impact too, but in some cases I think they're still worth it.</div>

