			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In general, one 32-byte update packet can update one row of nametable, one column of nametable, the entire palette, or two tiles in CHR RAM. Battletoads is an example of a game that animates the player character by updating whole frames of animation to CHR RAM, but then it also keeps rendering turned off for the top 16 or so scanlines so that it has time for a larger update. The technique is more common on Genesis, Super NES, and Game Boy Advance, all of which have hardware-assisted copying to VRAM.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
